==Swedish==
===Etymology===
Latin '''[[pro]]''', ''for'', + '''[[sit]]''', ''"may it be"'':  literally ''"may it be for (you)"'', ''"may it benefit (you)"''

===Interjection===
'''prosit!'''

#[[bless you]]! (''said to someone who has just sneezed'')

====Usage notes====
#Some say that Swedish speakers do not regard this as a real word.

